 of locally hosted applications.&nbsp; If we login with password, all works OK.&nbsp; As a workaround, locking screen and unlocking with password seems to resolve the issue without having to reboot. 
 &nbsp; 
 Additionally, when screen is locked and attempting to unlock screen with Windows Hello, a message is displayed that your credentials could not be verified. 
 &nbsp; 
 Any ideas? 
 &nbsp; 
 Thanks, 
 &nbsp; 
 Tommy 
