Good morning Vince,
&nbsp;
Thanks for letting me know that. In that case, that changes a bit.
&nbsp;
The steps that we need to follow for Azure AD joined devices are:
  We create a local admin account, if the device is already with one admin account, we can use that to take the hash. If the computer has been cleaned recently and it shows like the picture above, click "Domain join instead" and create a local admin account with a simple username and password, since this will be only to update the W10 pro to the latest version, then we'll need to run OOBE. Please do not add this device to the Gemini domain.  &nbsp;
Note: Before we run OOBE, we need to add the devices to the groups required which means Autopilot_AzurePC or the AutoPilot_Cloud_Devices. Users can be assigned or not to the devices.&nbsp;

Then, we provide a name to the device and a password:

&nbsp;
&nbsp;
When the OOBE is completed, users can sign in using their O365 accounts.
&nbsp;
I can add the devices to the group in Intune, do you know if they have admin accounts and if the OS is up to date?

