Hello Jerry and Brad,&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Sorry for the delay in answering back again.
&nbsp;
We have tried multiple times to fix the issue; however, we tried many things to resolve this issue.
&nbsp;
  Removed the Microsoft Account from Office and added it again.  I download SARa (Microsoft Tool) to determine any issues. Sara stated that it was a OneDrive problem and that it was not communicating with the correct path.  I did an Online Repair (It did not work)  I removed and installed office again.  I removed the Credentials of Office from Windows Credentials and asked Brad to sign in back again.  I modified the register key: Go to HKEY_CURRENT_USER &gt; Software &gt; Microsoft &gt;Office &gt; 16.0 &gt;Common &gt; Identity  I got an error from Event Viewer. Error: Microsoft.AAD.BrokerPlugin_cw5n1h2txyewy. Error Code: -2147024891  I reset OneDrive from factory settings.&nbsp;  &nbsp;
